esume Book Submissions: Deadline May 22nd (For all STEM junior, senior and grad students)   April 6 - May 22, 2020  12:00 AM - 12:00 AM    Deadline EXTENDED to May 22nd!  By virtually connecting with students and collecting resumes, ThinkChicago can directly share the Spring 2020 Resume Book with their partner companies actively searching for university talent.  WHO SHOULD APPLY: juniors, seniors and masters students currently enrolled in Chicago/Illinois-based universities, specifically STEM-related majors (engineering, computer science, etc) and those students who have a strong interest in tech entrepreneurship and/or working for a tech company.  WHAT STUDENTS CAN EXPECT:  EARLY CAREER PATHWAY; to connect with Chicago's leading tech and innovation companies - resumes will be shared with previous ThinkChicago company partners include (but not limited to): Relativity, tastytrade, Invenergy, CCC Information Services, OppLoans, Grubhub, SpotHero, Sprout Social, Cameo, and many others.  CAREER & INTERNSHIP OPPORTNITIES: via our ThinkChicago email newsletter sharing the latest news from Chicago’s leading technology and innovation companies  EARLY ACCESS: to upcoming ThinkChicago programs and activities (campus roadshow events, local events, etc)  Resumes will be shared with previous ThinkChicago company partners include (but not limited to): Relativity, tastytrade, Invenergy, CCC Information Services, OppLoans, Grubhub, SpotHero, Sprout Social, Cameo, and many others.  Apply here    Contact  Eliana Riley  312-355-5142  eliana@uic.edu     Date posted  Apr 6, 2020    Date updated  May 4, 2020                    UIC Logo        Engineering Career Center       Contact   851 S. Morgan St. | 800 SEO | Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-8374  rcconroy@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openin